main event: Multiple reports from witnesses describe bright, spherical or oval-shaped objects moving at high speeds and exhibiting unusual brightness and maneuverability.
interesting points: Witnesses observed the objects moving at speeds of up to 600 mph, which ruled out conventional aircraft.
The objects were described as brighter than the moon and emitted intense white light with no visible red or green lights.
One witness specifically ruled out conventional explanations for the observed phenomena.
The sightings were classified as 'ATC AR 14-10' cases, indicating they were related to unidentified aerial phenomena.
A witness with a background in meteorology was involved in reporting the sightings.
location: multiple locations including Gouzenko, K11 and Alexandria, VA
witnesses: multiple civilians and an Air Force officer
